pageContext.claim: “The Governor did bad things. Your far left Democrat Attorney General, Keith Ellison and your Democrat Governor tried to shut down our rally, silence the people of Minnesota, and take away your freedom and your rights.”
pageContext.analysis: "Not content to adhere to the state’s limit of 250 people, Trump representatives searched for a more accommodating city and venue," the Twin Cities Pioneer Press reported. "Trump officials and GOP state leaders targeted state leaders, blaming the “free speech-stifling dictates” of [Gov. Tim] Walz and [Attorney General Keith] Ellison....But Ellison’s office said it did nothing to interfere with the event, only asking that McNeilus [the original venue] have a COVID-19 preparedness plan if it were to host the rally. Trump campaign officials’ beef appeared to be with Rochester city officials, who didn't want to see a super spreader event in their community."
